## Coding Standards

- **Style**: Use ruff for linting and formatting, isort for imports
- **Testing**: All new code requires tests in `tests/`
- **Types**: Include type hints in function signatures
- **Docs**: Keep docstrings concise but informative
- **DRY**: Avoid duplication; centralize shared logic
- **Simplicity**: Prefer simple solutions over complex abstractions

## Workflow Requirements

### Before Committing

1. Run `./admin/lint.sh` - fix any errors
2. Run `./admin/format.sh` - format code
3. Run `./admin/test.sh` - ensure tests pass
4. Update `CHANGELOG.md` under `[Unreleased]`

### Pull Request Checklist

- [ ] Tests added/updated for changes
- [ ] Linting passes (`./admin/lint.sh`)
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed

